title: Sooronbay Jeenbekov - Wikipedia
snippet: Jeenbekov resigned on 15 October 2020. He stated as his official reason staying not being "worth the integrity of our country and agreement in society".

title: Kyrgyzstan: President Sooronbay Jeenbekov steps down
snippet: Kyrgyzstan’s president Sooronbay Jeenbekov announced his resignation in a desire to avoid further violence. Sadyr Japarov is the interim president.

title: Kyrgyz President Jeenbekov announces resignation - CGTN
snippet: "I do not want to go down in the history of Kyrgyzstan as a president who allowed bloodshed and shooting on its people. I have taken the decision to resign," said Jeenbekov in the statement released by his office.
